The concept immediately reminded me of Shikwa and Jawab-e-Shikwa. Beautifully executed!
Kudos to everyone for pouring their hearts out. Loved the inclusion of the bookshop and the elderly cat lady. I thought “2 am” alone was tugging at my heartstrings, and as if that was not enough, the flutist who was playing an impromptu “Kholo Kholo” at 10:51 just opened the floodgates. Thank you for this piece of magic, love for all.

snippet.textDisplay:
This is an absolute gem! The intricate details of the set design, the videography, the lighting, I mean every dust particle is exactly where It's supposed to be. I don't think I have seen a production like this since Michael Jackson's "Thriller." How Xulfi finds these artists, these diamonds in the sky, it's just amazing! Imagine two singers who have never met each other who wrote and sang their respective songs 5-6 years ago are now on this production which completes their story. It's like a beautiful picture torn in the middle and after years it's re-joined...just brilliant!

Congratulations and a BIG thank you to each and every member of this production and of course Coke Studio as the enabler. Xulfi bhai, you not only surprise us each time, but you also go up another 10 levels. We feel so proud of you and your team!
